The type locality is at ca. 1400 m asl in the Ba Na hills close to Đa Nẵng city (referred to as Tourane in the original description), central Vietnam. The species is also known form Nangongshan Mountain, Mengla County, Yunnan Province ( Xu 2000 ) (1525 m asl) and from Hunan Province (
Guenard and Dunn 2012
). In the places where it is known, specimens were collected from the ground in evergreen broadleaved forest. The new record from the Gutianshan National Nature Reserve, Zhejiang Province, is no exception in being from the same forest type albeit at lower elevation (890 m asl) and marks the easternmost distribution of the species. Thus, P. longigaster seems to be widespread in suitable forest habitats in south and east China and adjacent countries. No direct observations of biology and natural history are available.
